OL,3,CCampaigners 'devastated' as British
OL,4,CSign Language GCSE is scrapped
OL,6,F"More people knowing and using BSL is
OL,7,Fkey to breaking down the barriers some
OL,8,Fdeaf young people face. There's no
OL,9,Fquestion that they deserve to be able
OL,10,Fto achieve a formally recognised
OL,11,Fqualification in their own language."
OL,13,FShe added: "We'll continue to stand
OL,14,Fwith deaf young people on this. We're
OL,15,Fas determined as ever to make sure
OL,16,Fthat a BSL GCSE becomes a reality in
OL,17,FWales and are keen to work with
OL,18,FQualifications Wales to overcome the
OL,19,F'practical challenges' it describes."
