OL,3,CCampaigners 'devastated' as British
OL,4,CSign Language GCSE is scrapped
OL,6,FThe exams regulator, Qualifications
OL,7,FWales, had already delayed the
OL,8,Fintroduction of the new GCSE from 2026
OL,9,Fto 2027.
OL,11,FQualifications Wales said it had
OL,12,F"after careful consideration taken the
OL,13,Fdifficult decision to suspend the
OL,14,Fdevelopment of a made-for-Wales GCSE
OL,15,Fin British Sign Language".
OL,17,FInstead of the GCSE, learners will be
OL,18,Fable to work towards a new Skills for
OL,19,FLife qualification in BSL.
